        <h2>Case Note: Recruitment agency fails to remove all personal information</h2>
        
        <div class="quote-box">
          <p>A former client of a recruitment agency expressed a clear desire to have his online profile removed, which contained sensitive information such as his name, photo, qualifications, and personal interests.</p>
        </div>
        
        <p>Although the agency acted by deleting his name and photo, the remaining profile information was still accessible online, leading the man to discover that it was appearing in Google search results. This prompted significant concerns regarding the ongoing use of his personal information.</p>
        
        <div class="definition-box">
          <h3>Resolution</h3>
          <p>In response to these concerns, the recruitment agency acknowledged the situation and took appropriate action by completely removing the profile from their website. This decisive step ensured the protection of the man's personal information, leading to a satisfactory resolution of the issue and closure of the complaint.</p>
        </div>
